docs.lead_paragraph: We had a noble rain on Saturday night. Throughout the day it had been drizzly, or showery by turns. But with the evening a fine rain set in, which at midnight was a model. It was like a well. sustained poem, fill of music and exquisite in rhyme, as it pattered on the windows and rattled on the roof; it did one good like the healing from a full-voiced reader a chapter from the Iliad.
